Some life lately….Just tapping in to say it’s good. 

I’m grateful and blessed to have the opportunity to be alive, living, and experiencing authentic joy with ppl I love. We stumble around searching for something, the nagging nuanced little itch that won’t subside. Our collective burning desire, the existential question of purpose and meaning. Trust me when I say that I’m sure I know nothing…for that; opens me up to everything. 

- #life imitating #art

New direction…💚

Jack winthrop mostly paints large-scale paintings on canvas. Maneuvering between and eclectic range of styles and subjects, he challenges the conventional and explores the boundaries between fine art and subculture. By breaking down the human form, he creates work appearing like a mirror that transcends the filter we perceive as ourselves. His work “PEACE” arose from the techniques Jack Winthrop learned from, drawing, painting, and creating throughout his life by dissecting and dissolving them through abstraction. Winthrop deploys refined and sophisticated judgements through form, color, composition, balance, tension, and aesthetic, which he attributes to his education in the field of design. “PEACE” is the translation and transformation of the artists engrossment towards the human condition, which he visualizes in his works.

Recently I’ve been trying to push the “TOTEMS” series further and go much deeper into the work. Felt like I had a breakthrough during this piece. As each totem is representative of a spiritual energy and experience that is parallel to my own growth. The paintings have a way of reflecting something within me, sometimes I am unaware of it until they’re finished. As if I’m channeling a subconscious idea. Art is magical, the process of creation has truly been one of my greatest teachers in life. enjoying that all of you get to witness this journey/evolution through my videos and posts as well. Thank you for watching 🙋🏻‍♂️👨🏻‍🎨 #art #artwork #artist

I am excited to announce my artist residency w/ @biltrewards who commissioned three original paintings from me. They visited my studio and did an interview with me which I will be sharing soon! 

My current art and "Totems" series delves into art as spirituality or meaningful introspection. composing context around virtues, principles, states of being, perception, and energy I transcribe these characteristics with paint. Sampling different cultures and religions or belief systems while combining them within my own visual language and the symbolic nature that these totems represent. 

-I am breaking down form and color as it pertains to my current series in a new and totally abstract way. Jack implements and defines spontaneity, A flow state that emerges from the process of production and generation while focusing on the juxtaposition of form and monochromatic color palettes.
